TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,6,1);
$x1 = 3.14159265;
$y1 = -$a1*$x1;
$m1 = -$a1;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$PAR
Find the equation of the tangent line to the curve
 \[ y =   $a1 x \cos x  \]
at the point \( ( \pi , -$a1 \pi) \).
$PAR
The equation of this tangent line can be written in the form \( y = mx+b \) where
$PAR
\( m = \) \{ans_rule(20) \}
$PAR
and \( b = \) \{ans_rule(20) \}
EOT

$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

$ans = $y1 -$m1*$x1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

